title: Congratulating Tierney Wallace upon setting two age-group world records in winning three events at the 2010 Northeast Regional Single Lift Powerlifting Championships
fulltext:
LEGISLATIVE  RESOLUTION  congratulating Tierney Wallace upon setting two
age-group world records in winning three events at  the  2010  Northeast
Regional Single Lift Powerlifting Championships

WHEREAS,  Excellence  and  success in competitive sports can be achieved
only through strenuous practice,  nurtured  by  dedicated  coaching  and
strategic planning; and
  WHEREAS, It is the sense of this Legislative Body to recognize and pay
tribute  to  those esteemed individuals within the State of New York who
distinguish themselves through  outstanding  achievements  in  worldwide
athletic competition; and
  WHEREAS,  Attendant to such concern, and in full accord with its long-
standing traditions, this Legislative Body is justly proud to  congratu-
late Tierney Wallace upon setting two age-group world records in winning
three  events at the Northeast Regional Single Lift Powerlifting Champi-
onships; and
  WHEREAS, The event which was held at Johnson City Senior  High  School
on Saturday, May 29, 2010, drew about 80 different competitors from nine
states; and
  WHEREAS,  Tierney  Wallace's  overall  record  is outstanding; she was
loyally and enthusiastically supported by family, fans, friends and  the
community at large; and
  WHEREAS, An Endicott resident, Tierney Wallace picked up 281 pounds in
the deadlift competition in the women's 148-pound weight class, which is
a record for the 20-24-year-old age group; and
  WHEREAS,  Tierney  Wallace  also set a record with an 83-pound lift in
the strict curl; in addition, she also won the bench press contest; and
  WHEREAS, Sports competition instills the  values  of  self-motivation,
pride  and  accomplishment,  and  Tierney  Wallace  has  clearly  made a
contribution to the spirit of excellence which is  a  tradition  of  her
community; now, therefore, be it
  RESOLVED,  That  this  Legislative  Body pause in its deliberations to
congratulate Tierney Wallace upon setting two age-group world records in
winning three events at the Northeast Regional Single Lift  Powerlifting
Championships; and be it further
  RESOLVED, That a copy of this Resolution, suitably engrossed, be tran-
smitted to Tierney Wallace.
